metadata.name: SoulSea #236
metadata.description:
The Soul Sea

You look down and find that the ocean in your heart is a sine wave. 
The tide gently laps onto the shore.

The soul is the sea. You are the land. 
There are waves on the shore, and the waves are slices.

Gazing at the slices, you feel the coldness of the Arctic Ocean, the permafrost of the Antarctic Sea, the deep darkness of the bottomless sea.

Stay silent, hear the sound of the waves lapping at the innumerable shores far away.
Feel the soul of the digital ocean.

Interactivities:
> Key P: Pause
> Key S: Save
> Press and move mouseX: wave moves slower / faster

Che-Yu Wu

metadata.name: CHRONUS #44
metadata.description:
Following the use of simple shapes as the main element, combined with the alternation and overlapping of layers and blending modes, "CHRONUS" adds the temporal dimension as one of the elements that form what is seen.

Furthermore, the different gradations, associated with the play of lights and shadows, reveal the unusual as an image.

Nothing is just one thing.

#Main Features
- 13 color schemes ‚Äúzones‚Äù:

* Vascai, Shadow Sky and Bronze ‚Äì 12,5% chance
* Burnt Golden - 10% chance
* Lemonade - 8,5% chance
* Red Browned, Rec, Tif and Soldier - 7,5% chance
* Lushtemple and 80‚Äôs ‚Äì 5% chance
* BR - 2,5% chance
* B&W - 1,5% chance

- 3 canvas formats;
- 3 times of run;
- 3 patterns;
- 3 degrees of color saturation;

Obs.:
- The first 3 iterations will entitle you to 1 free edition of my next project on FxHash.
- The "STEEL" palette entitles you to 1 free edition of my next project on FxHash.
- The rendering process should take a few seconds, so enjoy the look of the circles in action.

september 14, 2022

Generative Token by Morbeck for fxhash.

metadata.name: adrift #246
metadata.description:
Take your entire life, full as it is with the vastness of your lived experiences ‚Äì and shape it into your cupped hands. Cherish this mesmerising world of yours as you would a ripe summer fruit, and behold at a glance its delicate yet dynamic balance ‚Äî one change here or there, no matter how microscopic, affects the entire course of your world. 

How will you receive this world ‚Äì its situations that overwhelm, its sights that awe, the catastrophes, the serenity, its steadfast commitment to the present? Will you look upon all of us here, adrift and fragile together, with love?


Adrift is a project that reminds us to make peace with our world ‚Äì with all worlds ‚Äì by stepping back to make space for an all-encompassing perspective.


------------


Created by Jacek Markusiewicz @jMarkusiewicz
Creative collaboration with Tender @tender_art

Click on the image for resolution options and to save a .png file. Saving higher resolutions may not work in some browsers; in these cases, right-click-save the image. All drawing and geometric methods are written by mrkswcz using javascript, except for the following:

The pseudorandom terrain generation uses Hydraulic-Erosion by Sebastian Lague, inspired by "Reconnaissance" by TENDER x Nat Sarkissian (MIT License).

For finding paths that simulate connections in terrain and potential locations of cities, a C# script was adapted from the article "Pathfinding Algorithms in C#" by Kristian Ekman published in Code Project licensed under The Code Project Open License (CPOL). The code was translated to javascript and simplified for performance.

Many pseudorandom effects are achieved with perlin-simplex by David Guttman and seedrandom by David Bau (both MIT Licenses)

For more information, please see the bundle.js.LICENSE.txt file included in the package.

The "heat death" event is a small tribute to lunarean's fxhash project. The code that generates the disintegration effect interprets a fragment of lunarean's code. Further contributions are its adaptation for 3d transformations and its recursive character that modifies certain parameters over time.

The project uses CPU for calculations and rendering ‚Äì generating the image requires up to 500MB of free RAM. Testing was performed across browsers and devices, but please make sure it works on your device before minting. Note that there are minor colour-intensity differences between different browsers.

metadata.name: Hyperspace interface #62
metadata.description:
Another one of my belowed GUI in retro-style
Fasten your seat belts, team! We are entering the hyperspace!

IMPORTANT! 
The work has two modes. At 100% page scale it is more stylized as a blurry retro.
You can zoom in to 125% for a crisper, cleaner look. This is done with CTRL + MOUSE SCROLL or with CTRL + "+"
You also need to refresh the page after zooming!

ALSO!
The best view is obtained in the aspect ratio of 1:1 or 4:3, in 16:9 the work requires too many resources and has nothing to show.

metadata.name: Fleur des Sinus #126
metadata.description:
Originally based on Alberto Burri's 1973- 1976 Screen Prints, then further iterated upon: Fleur des Sinus is meant to play with abstraction by designing larger than the canvas. Creating something that's clearly defined and pushing in just enough to find new compositions in section and intersection.

There are two possible modes, changing the shape of the flowers.
26 palettes are available, each composed of 4 colors: 104 colors in total.
A palette is picked for each edge flower, the center flower expresses itself with no inhibitions.
The Flowers are made up of between 4-10 petals.
The background pattern is 1-6 petal minimal dot flower patterns.

Press 's' to save the image in Live View.

metadata.name: Irregular #55
metadata.description:
Irregular is a generative art project made to loop without an end.
Each iteration creates a random noise distributed grid of points. This base grid is the final static output image. Once created, it enters a deformation loop based on a flow movement, which is distorted and returns to the origin with a breathing rhythm.

Responsive, zoom out browser window and refresh to get a larger output.
's' save the current canvas

Made with love, javascript and p5js
2022 Diego Pintos, see LICENSE.md

metadata.name: scratches & circles #113
metadata.description:
first fully coded generative artwork by @ndru_art made with p5.js

project features:
- up to 5 rows of 'scratches' at varying canvas heights & thickness
- scratches generated with random horizontal density and variance
- circles of varying sizes generated within a certain proximity of each row
- 5 different color palettes
- 'narrow scratches' feature defined by rows with a thickness value < 10

minters get 10% of secondary sales

special thanks to Orr Kislev for making his 'sketchy lines' code publicly available
